# expected-triples.nq — ground-truth N-Quads for the data-model fixture corpus.
#
# Format: N-Quads (https://www.w3.org/TR/n-quads/). One quad per line:
#   <subject> <predicate> <object> <graph> .
# Triples in the default graph omit the graph term:
#   <subject> <predicate> <object> .
#
# The IRIs and named graphs match exactly what the parser + ontology adapter
# (src/adapters/oxigraph_ontology_repository.rs) and graph adapter
# (src/adapters/oxigraph_graph_repository.rs) should emit when ingesting the
# `valid/` corpus.
#
# Ordering rule: sorted lexicographically by (G, S, P, O) within each section.
# Sections are separated by a blank line + comment header for human readers.
#
# Hash-prefixed comments are ignored by N-Quads parsers (Oxigraph,
# rio_turtle/oxttl, sophia all skip them).
#
# Predicate aliases used below:
#   rdf  : http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#
#   rdfs : http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#
#   owl  : http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#
#   xsd  : http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#
#   vc   : https://visionflow.dreamlab/ns/
#   prov : http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#
#
# ============================================================================
# 1. urn:visionflow:graph:knowledge — Pages, LinkedPages, NostrSignedPages
# ============================================================================

