<urn:visionflow:owl:class:humanist-architect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Humanist Architect" <urn:visionflow:graph:ontology:assert> .
<urn:visionflow:owl:class:humanist-architect> <https://visionflow.dreamlab/ns/description> "An architect whose practice is grounded in humanist scholarship — typically literate in Latin, conversant with the surviving texts of Vitruvius, and active across multiple liberal arts. Distinguished from craft-trained architects of the Gothic guilds by theoretical rather than purely empirical formation." <urn:visionflow:graph:ontology:assert> .
